ENTRY            D4435   20260123   20260508   20260508       D151
SUBENT        D4435001   20260123   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                 11         30
TITLE      Measurement of beta-particles to determine cross
           sections relevant to the weak r-process
AUTHOR     (S.R.Kovacs,T.N.Szegedi,A.Toth,A.Nemeth,M.K.Pal,
           E.Szilagyi,M.Braun,G.Gyurky,Z.Elekes,Z.Halasz,T.Szucs,
           G.G.Kiss)
INSTITUTE  (3HUNDEB,3HUNKOS)
REFERENCE  (J,NIM/A,1073,170272,2025)
           #doi:10.1016/j.nima.2025.170272
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3HUNDEB)
SAMPLE     Natural isotopic composition Kr gas cell target, and
           implanted solid-state target of 86Kr in Al backing.
DETECTOR   (SIBAR)
METHOD     (ACTIV) Cross section was measured by using charged
           particle activation method.
           (BSPEC) Activity measurement of the reaction products
           was done by Beta ray spectrometry based on Partially
           Depleted Silicon Surface Barrier Detector.
ERR-ANALYS (EN-ERR)
           Primary beam energy uncertainty (+/-0.05 MeV)
           (ERR-T)
           The total uncertainty of the cross-section values
           13-17% is estimated using the standard method, which
           involves taking the quadratic sum of the independently
           contributing parameters.
           (ERR-S,8.0,12.0) statistical uncertainty (8-12%)
           (ERR-1) beam intensity (3%)
           (ERR-2) detection efficiency (8%)
           (ERR-3,5.,8.) target thickness (5-8%)
STATUS     (TABLE,,S.R.Kovacs+,J,NIM/A,1073,170272,2025) Text(p.4)
HISTORY    (20260123C) TT
ENDBIB              30
COMMON               2          3
ERR-1      ERR-2
PER-CENT   PER-CENT
3.0        8.0
ENDCOMMON            3
